snippet: Google has for the first time agreed to legally binding changes to its search results after an antitrust investigation by European regulators.
abstract: European Commission accepts proposed settlement from Google following two-year inquiry into whether it abuses its dominance in online search; Google will now clearly label search results from its own properties, though company's basic algorithm will remain unchanged.
lead_paragraph: Google has for the first time agreed to legally binding changes to its search results after an antitrust investigation by European regulators.

headline.seo: Google and Europe Reach Deal on Search Results
headline.main: Europeans Reach Deal With Google on Searches
headline.print_headline: Europeans Reach Deal With Google On Searches
